title: $:/plugins/rimir/frontmatter/changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|0.1.4 |2026-05-14 |''Bug fix:'' `yaml.serialize()` now persists the tiddler `title` to YAML (was excluded alongside `text`/`type`/`bag`). The filename is a lossy reflection of the title — TW translates `:` and other filesystem-invalid characters to `_` on save, so deriving the title back from the filepath at load corrupts tiddlers whose title contains those characters. Symptom that motivated the fix: a `<parent.msg-title>.email` artifact (msg-import) whose parent title contained `:` would round-trip to a tiddler with `_`s in its title after a server restart, breaking the cascade transclusion from the parent .msg view template. Existing `.md` files saved before this fix don't have `title:` in their YAML — they'll be rewritten with the correct title on next save (e.g. by editing the tiddler in the wiki). Or hand-add a single `title: "..."` line to the YAML to recover immediately. Added serialize round-trip tests for colon-containing titles |
|0.1.3 |2026-04-27 |Declare hard dependent `theme` and `doc-template` as soft-dependent in plugin.info |
|0.1.2 |2026-04-07 |Fix icon: add intrinsic dimensions and maroon color for core-hook settings panel |
|0.1.1 |2026-03-31 |Auto-detect any `.md` with frontmatter, syncer-safe re-parse, two-pass architecture, smart title derivation, doc-template docs |
|0.1.0 |2026-03-30 |Initial release: YAML frontmatter for markdown files |
